  <Fragment slot="headline">BMI Calculator Guide: What Body Mass Index Means</Fragment>

  <p>BMI stands for body mass index. It is a quick way to compare weight relative to height.</p>
  <p>A BMI calculator is often used as a general screening tool, not as a complete picture of health.</p>

  <h2>How BMI Is Calculated</h2>
  <p>BMI uses height and weight in a formula that estimates weight relative to body size.</p>

  <h2>Why People Use BMI</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>It is fast and simple</li>
    <li>It gives a standard reference point</li>
    <li>It is commonly used in general health discussions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What BMI Does Not Tell You</h2>
  <p>BMI does not directly measure body fat, muscle mass, fitness, or overall health. It is a broad screening metric, not a diagnosis.</p>

  <h2>How to Use It Properly</h2>
  <p>Use BMI as one data point. If you want a quick height-and-weight reference, it is useful. If you want a complete health picture, it is not enough by itself.</p>

  <h2>Best Tool to Use</h2>
  <p>Use the <a href="https://mycalcstool.com/en/bmi-calculator"><strong>BMI Calculator</strong></a> to check your BMI and see the basic range instantly.</p>

  <h2>Final Takeaway</h2>
  <p>BMI is best used as a quick reference, not a final judgment about health. It is useful for screening, comparison, and general awareness.</p>
</BlogLayout>
